  "prompt": "How do you become more of a people person?",
  "response": "Here are some tips to become more of a people person:\n\n1. Practice active listening\n- Pay attention when others speak\n- Ask follow-up questions\n- Show genuine interest in people's stories\n\n2. Develop empathy\n- Try to understand others' perspectives\n- Be compassionate\n- Put yourself in their shoes\n\n3. Improve communication skills\n- Work on your conversation skills\n- Learn to read body language\n- Be approachable and friendly\n\n4. Build social confidence\n- Practice small talk\n- Challenge yourself to interact with new people\n- Start conversations in low-pressure situations\n\n5. Show genuine interest\n- Remember details people share\n- Ask open-ended questions\n- Be curious about others\n\n6. Work on your body language\n- Maintain eye contact\n- Smile\n- Use open postures\n- Offer a firm handshake\n\n7. Be positive\n- Avoid constant complaining\n- Share uplifting stories\n- Offer encouragement\n\n8. Practice emotional intelligence\n- Manage your own emotions\n- Be aware of how you make others feel\n- Respond thoughtfully\n\n9. Step out of your comfort zone\n- Attend social events\n- Join clubs or groups\n- Take classes\n\n10. Be authentic\n- Don't try to be someone you're not\n- Be honest and genuine\n- Let your personality shine",
